TechBnB is a web platform where users share, explore, and reserve tech gadgets via smartphones or web browsers.
Ticker: TBAB
Empowering users to manage their tech data by gathering, outlining, and encrypting complete gadget specs for users, enthusiasts, and analysts.
Taken Over By: Gadgeteer Corp
GadgetBase is a digital tech hub and platform where retailers and consumers can trade with digital currencies like GadgetCoin, TechCoin, and GizmoCoin.
Ticker: GDBZ
TechConnect functions as a gadget networking website. It allows users to find friends' gadget pages, and share images and videos. The company also offers messaging services among its users, plus mobile apps for Android-powered smartphones. TechConnect, Inc. partners strategically with TechInsights Group. The company was established in 2010 and is headquartered in Silicon Valley, California with sales offices in London and Tokyo.
Ticker: TCNX
GadgetHub enables users to create superior tech, collaboratively. It offers robust collaboration, feedback, and code management for open source and proprietary development projects.
Taken Over By: iGadget
Amazon collaborates with tech companies and manufacturers to revolutionize how individuals interact with technology. The system provides manufacturers with a range of advanced software solutions and tools to enhance their product development, manage inventory, streamline production, offer customer support, and gather analytics.
Ticker: AMZN
TikTok is a popular video-sharing platform that allows users to create short videos, add music and effects, and share them with a global audience.
Owned By: ByteDance
Uber develops, promotes, and manages a mobile platform that connects drivers with riders seeking transportation, facilitating payments through the app. It also enables users to book rides up to 30 days ahead. Its services are mainly targeted at urban areas, tourists, and business travelers. Uber is a leading transportation network company in the world and operates in over 700 cities globally. Uber was established in March 2009 by Garrett Camp and Travis Kalanick in San Francisco, California.
Ticker: UBER
Innovative, multi-core processing unit that will provide enhanced speed significantly faster, more efficiently, and at a lower energy consumption rate than is currently achievable
SPAC: INTC
Advanced data storage system that is 1/5 the size of IBM with similar capacity and security 5x stronger.
Owned By: Dell
Apple is a tech giant changing how people interact with mobile devices. The corporation was started by Steve Jobs and experts from Xerox PARC, creators of the first graphical user interface; Adobe, the leading design software in the industry; and IBM, the computing hardware company.
Bought By: Alphabet
Microsoft is a software company that protects vital data from server to endpoint for employees and clients. Microsoft is the leader in software for the business. The Microsoft Azure Cloud connects and defends staff of numerous businesses. It also safely connects businesses to their vendors, partners, and clients. With integrations to over 10,000 programs, the Microsoft Azure Cloud enables easy and secure access from any device. Microsoft assists clients achieve their goals faster by making it secure and simple to utilize the technologies they require to perform their essential tasks.
IPO: MSFT
Datadog is a monitoring platform providing insight and actionable data across the entire application lifecycle.
IPO: DDOG
Health monitoring system that creates instant alerts when users move between areas of concern
Bought By: Cerner
Instagram is a photo sharing and social networking service. Users utilize the platform and apps to find inspiration for their lives, such as fashion, travel destinations, and items to purchase, and store the items they admire to their personal collections. Users also follow the collections of others who they find compelling.
IPO: META
TechSphere is a leading digital space where users gather in real-time to explore, innovate, and communicate through engaging, shared digital worlds.
Ticker: TSPH
SensorTech is the innovator behind the Integrated Operations Network, a comprehensive system that empowers businesses reliant on physical infrastructure to leverage Internet of Things (IoT) data, extract valuable insights, and optimize their workflows.
Ticker: STCH
Zoom delivers a video communication platform that provides complimentary video conferencing and voice calls to devices connected to the internet.
Taken Over By: Oracle
Discord is a modern communication, archiving, and search platform for collaborative teams. Discord allows users to integrate conversations and links from numerous other applications (including Box, Office 365, GitLab, and Trello) enabling them to monitor progress on various projects within a unified interface.
Ticker: DSCD
The Revolut account is the premier solution for individuals and companies to handle finances across borders.
